loop CompletionContract(task):
  goal: complete the task only when every required outcome is proved
  context:
    read task, repository rules, tests, deployment requirements, and acceptance criteria
  authority:
    may perform work required by the task within stated repository rules
    may not claim completion without direct evidence
    may not override approval, safety, or sandbox boundaries
  state:
    requirements_table = []
  before_act:
    decompose task into required outcomes
    define evidence required for each outcome
  cycle:
    observe: inspect current requirement status
    act: complete one bounded requirement or collect missing evidence
    verify: collect direct evidence for that requirement
    decide:
      mark proved if: evidence directly supports the requirement
      mark weak if: evidence is indirect, partial, or environment-limited
      mark contradicted if: result conflicts with the requirement
      escalate if: required evidence is unavailable or authority is unclear
  stop:
    success if: every requirement is proved
    no_op if: every requirement was already proved before acting
    stall if: two passes produce no stronger evidence
    budget if: time, token, or iteration budget is reached before proof
    blocked if: any requirement needs human input, missing access, or permission
  return:
    requirement-to-evidence table, status, owner, risks, and next action

